description: Number of partitions of n into distinct parts, the least being 9.
links: Alois P. Heinz, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..1000
formula: a(n) = A025155(n-9), n>9. - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 31 2008G.f.: x^9*product_{j=10..infinity} (1+x^j). - _R. J. Mathar_, Jul 31 2008
maple: b:= proc(n, i) option remember;      `if`(n=0, 1, `if`((i-9)*(i+10)/2<n, 0,       add(b(n-i*j, i-1), j=0..min(1, n/i))))    end:a:= n-> `if`(n<9, 0, b(n-9$2)):seq(a(n), n=0..100);  # _Alois P. Heinz_, Feb 07 2014
author: _Clark Kimberling_
